{
  "text": "Also through this technique, [CITATION_1] showed that a specific band assigned to the DNA was altered after UVB-induced damage and that this alteration occurs independently of the source of DNA damage [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . For this reason, they proposed this band as an indicator of DNA damage in sperm. These results were later corroborated by other authors [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
